{ "cells": [ { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "# Fine-tune XLM-RoBERTa for Comorian Language\n", "\n", "This notebook fine-tunes XLM-RoBERTa on Comorian story data using Google Colab's free GPU.\n", "\n", "**Features:**\n", "- Uses free Google Colab GPU\n", "- Optimized for low-resource languages\n", "- Supports story data format\n", "- Automatic model saving to Google Drive\n", "- Progress tracking and visualization\n", "\n", "**Estimated Time:** 2-4 hours for training\n", "\n", "---" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 1: Setup and Installation\n", "\n", "First, ensure you're using a GPU. Go to **Runtime > Change runtime type > GPU**" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "# Check GPU availability\n", "import torch\n", "print(f\"GPU Available: {torch.cuda.is_available()}\")\n", "print(f\"GPU Name: {torch.cuda.get_device_name(0) if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'N/A'}\")\n", "print(f\"CUDA Version: {torch.version.cuda}\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "# Install required packages\n", "!pip install --upgrade transformers datasets torch tensorboard -q\n", "!pip install sentencepiece sacremoses -q\n", "print(\"✅ Installation complete!\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 2: Mount Google Drive\n", "\n", "This allows you to save your trained model and data" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "from google.colab import drive\n", "drive.mount('/content/drive')\n", "print(\"✅ Google Drive mounted!\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "# Create project directory in Google Drive\n", "import os\n", "project_dir = '/content/drive/MyDrive/comorian-mbert-project'\n", "os.makedirs(f'{project_dir}/data/raw', exist_ok=True)\n", "os.makedirs(f'{project_dir}/data/processed', exist_ok=True)\n", "os.makedirs(f'{project_dir}/models', exist_ok=True)\n", "print(f\"✅ Project directory created at: {project_dir}\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 3: Create Sample Comorian Story Data\n", "\n", "Add your story data here. For testing, we'll create sample data." ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "# Sample Comorian stories\n", "sample_stories = \"\"\"Hadithi ya Juma na Fahali\n", "\n", "Siku moja, Juma alikuwa anabakabaika jijini. Alikuwa ana njaa sana lakini hana pesa. Alitembea kwenye barabara na kumkuta rafiki yake Salim. Salim akamwambia, Juma, kwa nini unabakabaika? Juma akasema, Nana njaa sana lakini sina pesa ya kununua chakula. Salim akamwambia, Karibu nyumbani, mama yangu ameandaa chakula chazuri sana.\n", "\n", "Walitembea pamoja mpaka nyumba ya Salim. Mama wa Salim akamkaribisha Juma kwa furaha. Akaandaa chai na mkate wa kusambika. Juma akakula kwa haraka kwa sababu ya njaa. Baada ya kula, Juma akajuta na kusema Asante sana, mungu akubariki.\n", "\n", "Kutoka siku ile, Juma na Salim walikuwa marafiki mazuri. Kila siku walionana na kuzungumza. Juma alibadilika mwenyewe na kuanzia kufanya kazi. Baada ya mwezi mmoja, Juma alikuwa ana pesa. Akamshukuru Salim kwa msaada wake.\n", "\n", "Hadithi ya Fatima na Ndoto Yake\n", "\n", "Fatima alikuwa msichana mdogo lakini ana ndoto kubwa. Alitaka kuwa mwalimu ili kufundisha watoto. Wazazi wake wakamwambia, Ndoto yako ni nzuri lakini ya mbali sana. Lakini Fatima hakukataa. Alianza kusoma kwa bidii sana.\n", "\n", "Kila asubuhi alionana na mwalimu wake na kumwuliza maswali. Aliandika kumbukumbu za masomo yake. Usiku alisubiri kucheza kwa rafiki zake. Baada ya miaka mitatu, Fatima akamalizia shule. Wazazi wake walikuwa na furaha sana.\n", "\n", "Fatima akaanzia kufundisha watoto wadogo. Watoto wake wakamupendeleo sana kwa sababu alikuwa mwalimu mzuri. Baada ya miaka kadhaa, Fatima akawa mwalimu msaada katika shule kubwa. Ndoto yake ilikuwa imetekelezwa.\n", "\n", "Hadithi ya Babu na Akili Yake\n", "\n", "Babu alikuwa mzee mjinga sana. Alijua hadithi nyingi za zamani. Alijua jinsi ya kubunga nyumba nzuri. Alijua jinsi ya kuandaa malifu mazuri. Alijua jinsi ya kutengeneza njia nzuri kuelekea shambani.\n", "\n", "Jina la Babu liliitwa Mwanamisi. Wanamiji na wanawake walikuwa wanakuja kumwomba ushauri. Babu aliambia, Akili nzuri huanzia na kusikia vizuri. Mwanamisi alibadilika kuwa mjinga wa kijiji.\n", "\n", "Baada ya sana, Mwanamisi akawa mzee anayesikiliziwa na kila mtu. Watoto wake na wajukuu wake walijua akali yake. Akali yake ilikuwa akali nzuri ya kuzaliwa na akili nzuri.\n", "\n", "Hadithi ya Halima na Kazi Yake\n", "\n", "Halima alikuwa mwanamke hodari. Alikuwa anajua kubunga likwate nzuri sana. Anajua kubunga mbuzi nzuri. Anajua kusambika nyama nzuri. Anajua kutengeneza chai nzuri.\n", "\n", "Siku moja, Halima akajua kuwa ana watoto wajukuu. Akashangilia sana. Akabakia muda mrefu na watoto. Akawajifunzisha mambo mazuri ya maisha. Akawajifunzisha kuwa wageni wanapaswa kukamatwa kwa furnaha.\n", "\n", "Watoto wa Halima walijua yote kile aliyofundisha. Walijua kuwa maradhi ya moyo ni ya kufa. Walijua kuwa furaha ni akili nzuri. Halima akakufa kwa furaha.\n", "\n", "Hadithi ya Mdogo na Rafiki Yake\n", "\n", "Mdogo alikuwa mtoto mdogo. Rafiki yake aliekuwa Kubwa. Kubwa alikuwa mtoto mkubwa. Walipendana sana ingawa walikusumiwa kwa kila mmoja.\n", "\n", "Siku moja, Mdogo akajikuta kule Kubwa akipeleka mahali. Mahali hilo lilikuwa liko juu juu. Mdogo akaogopa sana. Lakini Kubwa akamwambia, Siogopi, nina wewe.\n", "\n", "Walipanda sana. Walipata matunda mazuri. Walipata maji mazuri. Walikula kwa furaha. Wakarudi kwa jioni.\n", "\n", "Wazazi wa Mdogo na Kubwa walikuwa na furaha. Waliona kuwa wanamiji hao waliweza kusaidiana. Walijua kuwa rafiki ni riziki.\n", """\n", "# Save sample data\n", "sample_data_path = f'{project_dir}/data/raw/comorian_sample_stories.txt'\n", "with open(sample_data_path, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n", "    f.write(sample_stories)\n", "\n", "print(f\"✅ Sample stories saved to: {sample_data_path}\")\n", "print(f\"Total characters: {len(sample_stories)}\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 4: Upload Your Own Data (Optional)\n", "\n", "If you have your own Comorian story data, upload it here" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "# OPTIONAL: Upload your own data file\n", "from google.colab import files\n", "\n", "print(\"To upload your own Comorian stories:\")\n", "print(\"1. Click the button below\")\n", "print(\"2. Select your .txt file\")\n", "print(\"\nFormat: One paragraph per line, or use [STORY_START] and [STORY_END] markers\")\n", "\n", "# Uncomment the line below to upload\n", "# uploaded = files.upload()" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 5: Prepare Data for Training" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "import re\n", "from pathlib import Path\n", "\n", "def clean_comorian_text(text):\n", "    \"\"\"Clean and normalize Comorian text\"\"\"\n", "    # Remove extra whitespace\n", "    text = re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text).strip()\n", "    \n", "    # Remove URLs\n", "    text = re.sub(r'http\\S+|www\\S+', '', text)\n", "    \n", "    return text\n", "\n", "def prepare_training_data(input_path, output_path, min_words=5):\n", "    \"\"\n", "    Prepare data for fine-tuning\n", "    Output: one paragraph per line\n", "    \"\"\"\n", "    with open(input_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n", "        content = f.read()\n", "    \n", "    # Split by double newlines (paragraphs)\n", "    paragraphs = content.split('\n\n')\n", "    \n", "    valid_paragraphs = []\n", "    for para in paragraphs:\n", "        para = clean_comorian_text(para)\n", "        \n", "        # Filter by word count\n", "        if len(para.split()) >= min_words:\n", "            valid_paragraphs.append(para)\n", "    \n", "    # Remove duplicates while preserving order\n", "    unique_paragraphs = []\n", "    seen = set()\n", "    for para in valid_paragraphs:\n", "        if para not in seen:\n", "            unique_paragraphs.append(para)\n", "            seen.add(para)\n", "    \n", "    # Write processed data\n", "    with open(output_path, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n", "        for para in unique_paragraphs:\n", "            f.write(para + '\n')\n", "    \n", "    return len(valid_paragraphs), len(unique_paragraphs)\n", "\n", "# Process the data\n", "raw_data_path = sample_data_path\n", "processed_data_path = f'{project_dir}/data/processed/comorian_stories_processed.txt'\n", "\n", "total, unique = prepare_training_data(raw_data_path, processed_data_path)\n", "\n", "print(f\"✅ Data Processing Complete!\")\n", "print(f\"Total paragraphs: {total}\")\n", "print(f\"Unique paragraphs: {unique}\")\n", "print(f\"Processed data saved to: {processed_data_path}\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "# Preview processed data\n", "with open(processed_data_path, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n", "    lines = f.readlines()[:5]\n", "\n", "print("Sample of processed data:")\n", "print("=" * 80)\n", "for i, line in enumerate(lines, 1):\n", "    print(f"{i}. {line.strip()[:100]}...")\n", "print("=" * 80)" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 6: Load Model and Tokenizer" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForMaskedLM\n", "\n", "# Use XLM-RoBERTa (better than mBERT for low-resource languages)\n", "model_name = \"xlm-roberta-base\"\n", "\n", "print(f\"Loading tokenizer: {model_name}\")\n", "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)\n", "\n", "print(f\"Loading model: {model_name}\")\n", "model = AutoModelForMaskedLM.from_pretrained(model_name)\n", "\n", "print(f\"✅ Model loaded successfully!\")\n", "print(f\"Model size: {model.num_parameters():,} parameters\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "# Test tokenizer on Comorian text\n", "test_text = \"Habari yako nzuri? Najifunza lugha ya Kikomori.\"\n", "tokens = tokenizer.tokenize(test_text)\n", "\n", "print(f\"Test text: {test_text}\")\n", "print(f\"Tokens: {tokens}\")\n", "print(f\"Number of tokens: {len(tokens)}\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 7: Prepare Dataset for Training" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "from transformers import TextDataset, DataCollatorForLanguageModeling\n", "\n", "print(\"Creating training dataset...\")\n", "\n", "train_dataset = TextDataset(\n", "    tokenizer=tokenizer,\n", "    file_path=processed_data_path,\n", "    block_size=256  # Larger block size for story data\n", ")\n", "\n", "print(f\"✅ Dataset created!\")\n", "print(f\"Number of training examples: {len(train_dataset)}\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "# Create data collator for masked language modeling\n", "data_collator = DataCollatorForLanguageModeling(\n", "    tokenizer=tokenizer,\n", "    mlm=True,  # Masked Language Modeling\n", "    mlm_probability=0.15  # 15% of tokens will be masked\n", ")\n", "\n", "print(\"✅ Data collator created!\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 8: Configure Training Arguments" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "from transformers import TrainingArguments\n", "\n", "# Configure training\n", "training_args = TrainingArguments(\n", "    output_dir=f\"{project_dir}/models/comorian-xlm-roberta\",\n", "    overwrite_output_dir=True,\n", "    num_train_epochs=3,  # Number of training epochs\n", "    per_device_train_batch_size=8,  # Batch size per GPU\n", "    gradient_accumulation_steps=1,  # Gradient accumulation\n", "    save_steps=100,  # Save checkpoint every 100 steps\n", "    save_total_limit=2,  # Keep only 2 latest checkpoints\n", "    logging_steps=50,  # Log every 50 steps\n", "    logging_dir=f\"{project_dir}/logs\",\n", "    learning_rate=2e-5,  # Learning rate\n", "    weight_decay=0.01,  # Weight decay\n", "    warmup_steps=500,  # Warmup steps\n", "    fp16=True,  # Mixed precision training (faster, less memory)\n", "    dataloader_num_workers=2,  # Number of workers for data loading\n", ")\n", "\n", "print(\"✅ Training arguments configured!\")\n", "print(f\"Output directory: {training_args.output_dir}\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 9: Train the Model\n", "\n", "⚠️ **This may take 2-4 hours depending on your data size**" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "from transformers import Trainer\n", "import time\n", "\n", "# Create trainer\n", "trainer = Trainer(\n", "    model=model,\n", "    args=training_args,\n", "    data_collator=data_collator,\n", "    train_dataset=train_dataset,\n", ")\n", "\n", "print(\"Starting training...\")\n", "print(\"=" * 80)\n", "\n", "# Start training\n", "start_time = time.time()\n", "trainer.train()\n", "end_time = time.time()\n", "\n", "training_time = (end_time - start_time) / 60\n", "print(\"=" * 80)\n", "print(f\"✅ Training complete!\")\n", "print(f\"Total training time: {training_time:.2f} minutes\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 10: Save the Fine-tuned Model" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "# Save model and tokenizer\n", "model_save_path = f\"{project_dir}/models/comorian-xlm-roberta-finetuned\"\n", "\n", "print(f\"Saving model to: {model_save_path}\")\n", "model.save_pretrained(model_save_path)\n", "tokenizer.save_pretrained(model_save_path)\n", "\n", "print(f\"✅ Model saved successfully!\")\n", "print(f\"Files saved:\")\n", "print(f\"  - pytorch_model.bin (model weights)\")\n", "print(f\"  - tokenizer.json\")\n", "print(f\"  - config.json\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 11: Test the Fine-tuned Model" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "from transformers import pipeline\n", "\n", "# Load the fine-tuned model for inference\n", "fill_mask = pipeline(\n", "    \"fill-mask\",\n", "    model=model_save_path,\n", "    tokenizer=tokenizer\n", ")\n", "\n", "# Test with Comorian text\n", "test_sentences = [\n", "    \"Habari yako [MASK]?\",\n", "    \"Najifunza lugha ya [MASK].\",\n", "    \"Juma alikuwa ana [MASK] sana.\",\n", "]\n", "\n", "print(\"Testing fine-tuned model on Comorian text:\")\n", "print(\"=" * 80)\n", "\n", "for test_text in test_sentences:\n", "    print(f\"\nInput: {test_text}\")\n", "    results = fill_mask(test_text)\n", "    print(\"Predictions:\")\n", "    for i, result in enumerate(results[:3], 1):\n", "        print(f\"  {i}. {result['sequence']} (score: {result['score']:.4f})\")" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 12: Load and Use Your Model Later\n", "\n", "Once trained, use this code to load and use your model:" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "# Code to load and use your fine-tuned model\n", "from transformers import AutoTokenizer, AutoModelForMaskedLM\n", "\n", "# Load from Google Drive\n", "model_path = "/content/drive/MyDrive/comorian-mbert-project/models/comorian-xlm-roberta-finetuned"\n", "\n", "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_path)\n", "model = AutoModelForMaskedLM.from_pretrained(model_path)\n", "\n", "print(\"✅ Model loaded from Google Drive!\")\n", "\n", "# Use for predictions\n", "from transformers import pipeline\n", "fill_mask = pipeline(\"fill-mask\", model=model, tokenizer=tokenizer)\n", "\n", "# Your Comorian text here\n", "result = fill_mask(\"Habari yako [MASK]?\")\n", "print(result)" ] }, { "cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": [ "## Step 13: Training Summary & Next Steps" ] }, { "cell_type": "code", "execution_count": null, "metadata": {}, "outputs": [], "source": [ "print(\"\""\n
" + "\" + "╔════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n" + "║           🎉 TRAINING COMPLETE! 🎉                              ║\n" + "╚════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n" + "\n📊 SUMMARY:\n   ✅ Model: XLM-RoBERTa (fine-tuned for Comorian)\n   ✅ Training epochs: 3\n   ✅ Saved to: {}/models/comorian-xlm-roberta-finetuned\n\n📁 PROJECT STRUCTURE:\n   Google Drive/comorian-mbert-project/\n   ├── data/\n   │   ├── raw/\n   │   │   └── comorian_sample_stories.txt\n   │   └── processed/\n   │       └── comorian_stories_processed.txt\n   ├── models/\n   │   ├── comorian-xlm-roberta/...\n   │   └── comorian-xlm-roberta-finetuned/...\n   └── logs/\n       └── (training logs)\n\n🚀 NEXT STEPS:\n   1. ✅ Download your model from Google Drive\n   2. ✅ Use it for downstream tasks (classification, NER, etc.)\n   3. ✅ Fine-tune further with more data\n   4. ✅ Share your model on Hugging Face Hub\n\n💡 IMPROVEMENTS:\n   - Add more Comorian story data\n   - Train for more epochs (5-10)\n   - Increase batch size if GPU memory allows\n   - Combine with other NLP tasks (classification, etc.)\n\n📚 RESOURCES:\n   - Hugging Face: https://huggingface.co/\n   - Transformers Docs: https://huggingface.co/docs/transformers/\n   - Model Hub: https://huggingface.co/models\n\n"\n   )